<h2 id="key-features">🔧 Key Features Compared</h2>

<h3>Data Integration and CDP Capabilities</h3>

Klaviyo functions as a lightweight CDP, ingesting data from your ecommerce platform, website tracking, point of sale systems, and third-party apps. The platform creates unified customer profiles that update in real-time, enabling segments like "customers who browsed product X but purchased product Y within 30 days."

Omnisend integrates with standard ecommerce platforms but lacks custom event tracking and predictive modeling. You're working with purchase and email engagement data primarily.

Postscript focuses on SMS-relevant data — phone number acquisition, message engagement, compliance status — with limited email behavior tracking since email is a newer feature.

<h3>Automation and Flow Building</h3>

Klaviyo's flow builder is the most sophisticated, supporting conditional splits based on any data point, A/B testing within flows, and complex branching logic. The learning curve is real — budget 20-40 hours to build a comprehensive automation suite.

Omnisend offers pre-built workflow templates that cover 80% of use cases. Their automation editor is simpler but limits complex logic. Fine for most operators, frustrating for advanced marketers.

Postscript's conversation flows excel at two-way communication. The platform can route customer replies to support teams, trigger automated responses based on keywords, and manage compliance automatically. For SMS, it's superior; for email automation, it's basic.

<h3>Segmentation and Targeting</h3>

Klaviyo supports unlimited segment conditions with AND/OR logic, predictive attributes (expected date of next order, predicted lifetime value, churn risk), and real-time segment updates. We've built segments with 15+ conditions for enterprise clients.

Omnisend allows solid segmentation based on purchase behavior and email engagement but lacks predictive attributes and limits condition complexity.

Postscript segments by SMS engagement, purchase behavior, and custom tags. Adequate for text campaigns, limited for sophisticated targeting.

<h3>Reporting and Attribution</h3>

Klaviyo's attribution modeling tracks email and SMS influence on purchases with adjustable attribution windows (default 5-day click, 24-hour open). The benchmarks dashboard compares your performance against similar businesses.

Omnisend provides campaign and automation revenue tracking but less granular attribution. Their reports are clean and actionable without being overwhelming.

Postscript's SMS attribution is strong, tracking per-message revenue with conversation-level reporting. Email reporting is functional but basic.

